   "source": [
    "The synthetic generator below stands on its own — nothing above is required for it to run.\n",
    "If some downloads failed (network, dead mirror, placeholder URL), that has **no effect** on\n",
    "the data the models see. Proceed to Step 2."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a630b9d6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Step 2 — Generate the synthetic first-trimester cohort\n",
    "\n",
    "The data layer proper. We fabricate **800 patients** (~22% pregnancy loss), each with **2–5\n",
    "longitudinal ultrasound scans**, from published clinical reference equations plus programmed,\n",
    "label-dependent latent biology.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Biological basis (literature-derived curves):**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Variable | Model | Reference |\n",
    "|----------|-------|-----------|\n",
    "| **CRL** (crown-rump length) | polynomial in GA | Robinson & Fleming 1975; Hadlock 1992 |\n",
    "| **GS** (gestational sac) | exponential growth | Nyberg 1987; Hellman 1969 |\n",
    "| **FHR** (fetal heart rate) | parabolic rise-then-plateau, peak ~wk 9 | Doubilet & Benson 1995 |\n",
    "| **YSD** (yolk sac diameter) | grows wk 5–10 then involutes | Blaas 1995; Cyr 1988 |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Design principles:** patient-level latent factors (growth / heart / placenta / noise);\n",
    "label-dependent but **overlapping** distributions (so classification is non-trivial);\n",
    "autoregressive scan-to-scan dependency; correlated maternal features; clinically plausible,\n",
    "GA- and outcome-dependent missingness; all values clamped to first-trimester ranges."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "29e1aff5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 2.1 Configuration & reproducibility"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "490e8a1d",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-07-05T12:58:16.724165Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-07-05T12:58:16.724099Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-07-05T12:58:16.726939Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-07-05T12:58:16.726601Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
