   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "### ✅ Layer 6 (Explainability & Paper Artifacts) complete\n",
    "\n",
    "- **FETA** temporal + maternal→time attention extracted per test patient and summarised by week.\n",
    "- **PREG-Net** node importance and edge attention extracted; learned edge weights compared against the\n",
    "  hand-designed physiological rationale.\n",
    "- **Case studies** for TP / TN / FP / FN with per-patient attention drivers.\n",
    "- Tables + Markdown written to `results/explainability/`.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "## 🎉 Notebook complete — full pipeline in one place\n",
    "\n",
    "| Layer | What it does |\n",
    "|-------|--------------|\n",
    "| 1 · Data | Generate the synthetic first-trimester cohort from literature growth curves |\n",
    "| 2 · Dataset & Graph | Stratified split, train-only normalization, knowledge-guided graph |\n",
    "| 3 · Models | FETA-Transformer, PREG-Net, and two ensembles (pure PyTorch) |\n",
    "| 4 · Training | One unified `Trainer` fits all four via `collate_mode` |\n",
    "| 5 · Evaluation | Test metrics, ROC/PR, confusion matrices, bootstrap CIs vs. 5 baselines |\n",
    "| 6 · Explainability | Attention → interpretability tables, figures, case studies |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Honest scope.** This is a reproducible *methods demonstration on 100% synthetic data* — it shows the\n",
    "architectures behave as designed, that the ensemble combines complementary views, and that the models\n",
    "are interpretable. It is **not** clinical evidence.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Still open** (deliberately not in this notebook): k-fold **cross-validation** and **statistical\n",
    "tests** (DeLong / McNemar / calibration) to make the model ranking statistically defensible, and\n",
    "**ablation** experiments (which the repo has not yet built — any ablation numbers today would be\n",
    "placeholders)."
   ]
  }
 ],
